<h1>dispatch_policy playground</h1>
<p class="muted">
  Every form below enqueues real jobs through the gem. Submit any of
  them, then watch <a href="/dispatch_policy">the admin dashboard</a>
  to see the partitions, gates, and tick samples react.
</p>

<h2>Single-gate basics</h2>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "slow_external_api",
  title: "SlowExternalApiJob — :throttle per endpoint",
  desc:  "Token bucket per ctx[:endpoint_id]. Bursts admit up to the bucket size, then drip at rate/per.",
  defaults: { endpoint_id: "ep-1", rate: 6, per: 60 } %>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "bulk_account",
  title: "BulkAccountJob — :concurrency per account",
  desc:  "Caps in-flight per ctx[:account_id]. New admissions wait until the cap clears.",
  defaults: { account_id: "acct-1", max: 3 } %>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "mixed",
  title: "MixedJob — :throttle + :concurrency on a composite scope",
  desc:  "Both gates use the policy partition_by 'ep:E|acct:A' so neither bucket nor cap is diluted.",
  defaults: { endpoint_id: "ep-1", account_id: "acct-1", rate: 10, per: 60, max: 2 } %>

<h2>Scheduling</h2>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "perform_in",
  title: "PerformInJob — set(wait:) round-trip",
  desc:  "Schedules each job N seconds in the future. Verifies the gem preserves scheduled_at across the staging round-trip.",
  defaults: { key: "k1" },
  default_count: 1,
  hide_batch: true,
  show_wait: true %>

<h2>Reliability</h2>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "retry_flaky",
  title: "RetryFlakyJob — retry_strategy: :restage",
  desc:  "Job raises with probability fail_rate. ActiveJob retries; the policy's :restage strategy puts retries back through the gates instead of bypassing them.",
  defaults: { key: "k1", fail_rate: 0.7 } %>

<h2>Stress tests</h2>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "high_throttle",
  title: "HighThrottleJob — rate=10k/min, almost unconstrained",
  desc:  "Bucket fills almost instantly; the limiter is the worker pool. Used to measure tick duration, admit batch saturation, and forwarder throughput under load.",
  defaults: { endpoint: "hot", rate: 10_000 },
  default_count: 500 %>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "high_concurrency",
  title: "HighConcurrencyJob — max=100, very short jobs",
  desc:  "max=100 with 100ms perform. Inflight count rises toward 100; tick duration stays low.",
  defaults: { bucket: "hot", max: 100 },
  default_count: 500 %>

<h2>Architecture demos</h2>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "sharded",
  title: "ShardedJob — shard_by",
  desc:  "queue_as derives 'shard-N' from account_id; the policy mirrors that as shard_by. Run one DispatchTickLoopJob per shard to admit in parallel.",
  defaults: { account_id: "acct-A", max: 5 },
  default_count: 80 %>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "fairness_demo",
  title: "FairnessDemoJob — in-tick EWMA reorder + tick_admission_budget",
  desc:  "Five tenants, fair_share=ceil(30/N). With an uneven backlog, cold tenants drain in 1–2 ticks while the hot one progresses at the capped rate.",
  defaults: { tenant: "hot" },
  default_count: 100 %>

<%= render "dispatch_form",
  kind:  "adaptive_demo",
  title: "AdaptiveDemoJob — :adaptive_concurrency + fairness (composed)",
  desc:  "Adaptive cap (initial_max=3, target_lag_ms=500) plus in-tick fairness (half_life=20s, tick_admission_budget=30). admit_count per tenant = min(fair_share, current_max - in_flight). Adaptive shrinks the cap on saturation; fairness keeps cold tenants from waiting behind the hot one. Use the Storm form below to drive both at once.",
  defaults: { tenant: "acme" },
  default_count: 50 %>

<h2>Storm — multi-partition stress generator</h2>

<%= form_with url: storms_path, method: :post, local: true, html: { class: "dispatch" } do |f| %>
  <h3>StormJob — flood many tenants with a triangular distribution</h3>
  <p class="desc">
    For <em>duration</em> seconds, enqueue the chosen target for many
    distinct <code>acc_1</code>..<code>acc_N</code> accounts with weight =
    account number (so <code>acc_N</code> is N× more likely than
    <code>acc_1</code>). Exercises the admin UI, fairness reorder, and
    adaptive cap with hundreds of partitions and a skewed distribution.
  </p>
  <div class="fields">
    <label>
      target
      <%= f.select :target,
            [
              ["AdaptiveDemoJob",     "adaptive_demo"],
              ["FairnessDemoJob",     "fairness_demo"],
              ["HighThrottleJob",     "high_throttle"],
              ["HighConcurrencyJob",  "high_concurrency"]
            ] %>
    </label>
    <label>
      num_accounts
      <%= f.number_field :num_accounts, value: 100, min: 1, max: 2_000 %>
    </label>
    <label>
      duration (s)
      <%= f.number_field :duration_seconds, value: 60, min: 1, max: 600 %>
    </label>
    <label>
      batch_size
      <%= f.number_field :batch_size, value: 20, min: 1, max: 200 %>
    </label>
    <button type="submit">Start storm</button>
  </div>
<% end %>
